    <main class="container">
        <section>
            <h1 id="dish"> Garlic Bread </h1>
            <img src="https://encrypted-tbn0.gstatic.com/images?q=tbn:ANd9GcRG2YuAsOGPlmnBaZDbJ0cF8WuupIJmLV-IxA&usqp=CAU" alt="garlic bread" class="image__dish">
            <p class="dish__intro">The following steps are the steps for cooking perfect and delicious <strong> Garlic Bread </strong></p>
            <br>
            <h2 class="ingredients__title heading" >Ingredients: </h3>
                <ol class="ingredients__list">
                    <li class="ingridient">1 16-ounce (450 g) loaf Italian bread or French bread</li> 
                    <li class="ingridient">1/2 cup (1 stick, 112 g) unsalted butter, softened</li> 
                    <li class="ingridient">2 large cloves garlic, smashed and minced</li> 
                    <li class="ingridient">1 heaping tablespoon chopped fresh parsley</li> 
                    <li class="ingridient">1/4 cup (25 g) freshly grated Parmesan cheese (optional)</li> 
                    </ol>
            <h2 class="procedure__title heading"> Steps To Follow:- </h2>    
                <ul class="procedure__list">
                    <li class="steps"> <u> <em class="step"> Step 1:</em> </u>Preheat oven to 350°F </li>
                    <li class="steps"> <u> <em class="step"> Step 2:</em> </u>Cut the loaf in half, horizontally. Mix the butter, garlic, and parsley together in a small bowl. Spread butter mixture over the the two bread halves. </li>
                    <li class="steps"> <u> <em class="step"> Step 3:</em> </u> Place on a sturdy baking pan (one that can handle high temperatures, not a cookie sheet) and heat in a 350°F (175°C) oven for 10 minutes.</li>
                    <li class="steps"> <u> <em class="step"> Step 4:</em> </u>  Remove pan from oven. Sprinkle Parmesan cheese over bread if you want. Return to oven on the highest rack.</li>
                    <li class="steps"> <u> <em class="step"> Step 5:</em> </u> Remove from oven, let cool a minute. Remove from pan and use a bread knife to cut into 1-inch thick slices. Serve immediately.</li>
                   </ul>
        </section>

